          "attributes": {
            "response": "The timezone in Tokyo is Japan Standard Time (JST), UTC+9. This makes Tokyo usually 14 hours ahead of New York when New York is on Eastern Standard Time (EST) and 13 hours ahead during Eastern Daylight Time (EDT). For daily video calls, this means:\n\n- **Morning in New York (e.g., 9 AM EST)**: Late evening in Tokyo (11 PM JST).\n- **Afternoon in New York (3 PM EST)**: Very early morning in Tokyo (5 AM JST).\n- **Evening in New York (9 PM EST)**: Mid-day in Tokyo (11 AM JST).\n\nFor practicality, scheduling calls when it's late evening in New York aligns with Tokyo's mid-morning, this tends to be the most convenient overlap."
